1
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:03,723
If our gods and our hopes
are nothing but scientific phenomena,

2
00:01:03,797 --> 00:01:08,461
then it must be said that our love
is scientific as well -“L'Eve Future"

3
00:01:13,339 --> 00:01:15,603
[sirens, city sounds]

4
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:21,971
[helicopter approaching]

5
00:01:54,347 --> 00:01:58,681
[over radio] Repo 202 to Control.
Arrived at target airspace.

6
00:01:58,751 --> 00:02:01,618
Commencing data relay.

7
00:02:08,294 --> 00:02:10,819
[background radio chatter]

8
00:02:16,703 --> 00:02:19,228
[people shouting]

9
00:02:24,944 --> 00:02:27,174
[loud crashing]

10
00:02:44,397 --> 00:02:46,388
[Batou] Fill me in.

11
00:02:46,466 --> 00:02:51,403
The perp killed the owner 52 minutes
ago, at crime scene #1, then took off.

12
00:02:51,471 --> 00:02:56,374
Ambushed and murdered two cops
at crime scene #2, an unmapped alley.

13
00:02:56,442 --> 00:03:00,970
All access points are blocked.
We storm it in 2 minutes.

14
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,842
That's the cyborg cop
from Section 9.

15
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:11,323
Keep your distance. I hear his bum luck
catches like the plague.

16
00:03:11,391 --> 00:03:16,454
E-police want to horn in on us.
They're asking for a data link.

17
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:19,157
First it's Public Safety,
now the E-Police.

18
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:21,325
Decline their request respectfully.

19
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:35,545
[faint footsteps]

20
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:55,398
[electronic beeping]

21
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:47,746
[crash]

22
00:04:55,395 --> 00:04:57,420
[woman] Help me.

23
00:04:57,497 --> 00:05:00,125
Help me.

24
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:12,039
[stretching, tearing]

25
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:20,218
[explosion]

26
00:05:26,359 --> 00:05:30,056
[singing in Japanese]

27
00:09:05,845 --> 00:09:10,282
[recorded voice] We've had eight cases
of gynoids murdering their masters.

28
00:09:10,349 --> 00:09:14,046
After each killing, they self-destruct,
electronic brains reformatted.

29
00:09:14,921 --> 00:09:20,052
In each case, the model in question
is Locus Solus #2052, “Hadaly” type.

30
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:22,686
A prototype developed for testing,

31
00:09:22,762 --> 00:09:25,526
they were provided free of charge
to contractors.

32
00:09:25,598 --> 00:09:28,260
Now, they've recalled
all the prototypes.

33
00:09:28,334 --> 00:09:31,235
According to their most recent report,

34
00:09:31,304 --> 00:09:35,866
they've identiﬁed no defects
in either software or hardware.

35
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:49,316
You get all that?

36
00:09:49,889 --> 00:09:53,416
Manufacturer's latest gynoids
go berserk, attacking their owners,

37
00:09:53,492 --> 00:09:56,757
company panics
and recalls every one.

38
00:09:56,829 --> 00:09:59,821
They can expect lawsuits
by bereaved families,

39
00:09:59,899 --> 00:10:03,266
inevitable liability trials
and mammoth damage awards.

40
00:10:03,336 --> 00:10:06,703
I get it all
except why Section 9 is involved.

41
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:08,262
You get it?

42
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:13,406
What you call getting it
may be just wishful thinking.

43
00:10:13,479 --> 00:10:17,074
Right now, Section 9's involved
for two reasons.

44
00:10:17,149 --> 00:10:20,846
First, not one single family
has filed a lawsuit.

45
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:25,721
In every case they've settled
with Locus Solus out of court.

46
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:29,727
Second, the victims
included a politician

47
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:33,322
and a retired Public Safety official.

48
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:35,629
Because terrorism's a possible motive,

49
00:10:35,701 --> 00:10:40,400
it's our job to consider
if it's a matter for Section 9.

50
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:43,874
lshikawa and Azuma
are getting background on the victims.

51
00:10:43,943 --> 00:10:46,776
You two check out the gynoids.

52
00:10:47,513 --> 00:10:50,778
[Aramaki] No questions. Go.

53
00:11:03,229 --> 00:11:06,926
Just for the record,
I didn't volunteer for this.

54
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:11,963
There's no way
I'll measure up to the Major.

55
00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:14,632
That's beside the point.

56
00:11:14,707 --> 00:11:17,198
I hear she's still listed as missing.

57
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:27,946
[Batou] The Major could only call
her brain and her ghost her own.

58
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:32,116
Although even she doubted
whether they were real.

59
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:35,160
Her brains and hardware
were government property

60
00:11:35,227 --> 00:11:38,390
and her entire memory,
including the classified information,

61
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:40,932
were part of the deal.

62
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,094
The top brass only cares about
recovering that memory.

63
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:47,037
Her life is not an issue for them.

64
00:11:50,176 --> 00:11:52,667
So, where do we start?

65
00:11:52,745 --> 00:11:56,704
[Batou] Locus Solus is located
in the northern frontier.

66
00:11:56,782 --> 00:12:00,013
The first step is to check in
with local Forensics.

67
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:03,055
POLICE

68
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:09,323
[background chatter]

69
00:12:27,713 --> 00:12:30,807
[female voice on loudspeaker]

70
00:12:33,352 --> 00:12:34,614
You guys...

71
00:12:34,687 --> 00:12:37,383
About the gynoid
this guy wasted yesterday...

72
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:40,357
She cost us two young officers.

73
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:43,088
Don't tell me you want her back?

74
00:12:43,162 --> 00:12:46,529
That's part of what
we've come to determine.

75
00:12:50,503 --> 00:12:53,802
Forensics is up on 19,
a right at the end of the hall.

76
00:12:53,873 --> 00:12:58,503
- Need a guide?
- No thanks, we'll skip the tour.

77
00:12:59,545 --> 00:13:03,777
“Birds never peck
at green persimmons,

78
00:13:03,849 --> 00:13:07,307
they wait until the fruit is ripe."

79
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:21,664
[metallic crash]

80
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:24,328
[elevator creaking]

81
00:13:26,939 --> 00:13:30,204
you would've had a choice word or two
for guys like us

82
00:13:30,276 --> 00:13:33,074
swooping down
to horn in on your case.

83
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:37,605
[Togusa] That's why it's so irritating.
It's like watching my old self.

84
00:13:37,683 --> 00:13:38,672
[chuckling]

85
00:13:38,751 --> 00:13:43,085
“It is no use to blame the looking glass
if your face is askew.

86
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:48,286
The mirror is not an instrument
of enlightenment but of illusion."

87
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:53,059
Well, neither of us has looks
worth staring at in the mirror.

88
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:56,094
[door opens]

89
00:14:07,413 --> 00:14:09,973
[bubbling]

90
00:14:16,889 --> 00:14:18,857
[electronic whirring]

91
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:38,906
[Haraway] You can come all you want,
I'm not sharing this investigation.

92
00:14:38,978 --> 00:14:41,572
And if you're too persistent,
I'll have you detained.

93
00:14:42,648 --> 00:14:46,914
l'm Togusa, Public Safety Section 9.
This scary-looking fellow...

94
00:14:46,986 --> 00:14:50,547
Blew her apart with double-O buckshot.

95
00:14:52,157 --> 00:14:57,094
A 50 caliber hollow point
would've left her easier to reconstruct.

96
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:04,597
She wasted 3 people,
two of 'em cops.

97
00:15:04,670 --> 00:15:09,607
She was trying to commit suicide
before you shot her. Isn't that right?

98
00:15:27,393 --> 00:15:30,851
- "Commit suicide" meaning... Miss...
- [Haraway] Haraway.

99
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:35,299
Miss Haraway, how exactly
would a robot kill itself?

100
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:38,566
By intentionally malfunctioning,

101
00:15:38,637 --> 00:15:42,801
these gynoids are capable of
self-authorizing attacks against humans.

102
00:15:42,875 --> 00:15:47,539
This liberates them from Moral Code #3.

103
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:52,175
[Togusa] Which stipulates, “Maintain
existence without injuring humans."

104
00:15:52,251 --> 00:15:55,778
lsn't “self-destruction” more accurate?

105
00:15:56,188 --> 00:15:58,452
[exhaling]

106
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:03,652
If you assume differences between
humans and machines are obvious.

107
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:07,130
[Togusa] Are such “suicides”
confined to a particular model?

108
00:16:07,199 --> 00:16:09,463
[Haraway] Not necessarily.

109
00:16:09,535 --> 00:16:14,165
In recent years we've seen a surge
of robot related problems,

110
00:16:14,239 --> 00:16:16,969
especially among the “pets”.

111
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:20,141
[Togusa] The cause?

112
00:16:20,212 --> 00:16:23,739
[Haraway] E-brain contamination
from microbes and viruses,

113
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:29,516
human production errors,
functional defects from wear-and-tear.

114
00:16:29,588 --> 00:16:32,523
- Take your pick, but...
- [Togusa] But?

115
00:16:32,591 --> 00:16:38,359
[Haraway] I say it's because humans
discard robots once they're redundant.

116
00:16:38,430 --> 00:16:41,228
When owners trade up to newer models,

117
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:48,001
some of those abandoned
become vagrants, and degenerate.

118
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:53,109
Perhaps it’s a protest
against their own obsolescence.

119
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,440
Absurd.

120
00:16:57,216 --> 00:16:59,741
[Haraway] Humans are different
from robots.

121
00:16:59,818 --> 00:17:03,515
That’s an article of faith,
like black isn't white.

122
00:17:03,589 --> 00:17:07,150
It’s no more helpful than the basic fact
that humans aren’t machines.

123
00:17:12,331 --> 00:17:17,291
Unlike industrial robots, the androids
and gynoids designed as“pets,"

124
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:21,135
weren't designed along utilitarian
or practical models.

125
00:17:22,107 --> 00:17:24,541
Instead, we model them
on a human image,

126
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:29,343
an idealized one at that.

127
00:17:30,616 --> 00:17:35,849
Why are humans so obsessed
with recreating themselves?

128
00:17:49,968 --> 00:17:53,369
- [Haraway] Do you have children?
- A daughter.

129
00:17:53,439 --> 00:17:55,430
[Haraway] Children have been excluded

130
00:17:55,507 --> 00:17:57,975
from the customary standards
of human behavior,

131
00:17:58,043 --> 00:18:01,376
if you define humans as beings
who possess a conventional identity

132
00:18:01,447 --> 00:18:03,745
and act out of free will.

133
00:18:04,183 --> 00:18:08,950
Then what are children who endure
in the chaos preceding maturity?

134
00:18:09,021 --> 00:18:13,583
They differ profoundly from “humans,”
but they obviously have human form.

135
00:18:13,659 --> 00:18:20,588
The dolls that little girls mother,
are not surrogates for real babies.

136
00:18:20,666 --> 00:18:25,126
Little girls aren't so much
imitating child rearing,

137
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:30,198
as they are experiencing something
deeply akin to child rearing.

138
00:18:30,275 --> 00:18:32,675
What on earth are you talking about?

139
00:18:32,744 --> 00:18:36,111
[Haraway] Raising children
is the simplest way

140
00:18:36,181 --> 00:18:40,777
to achieve the ancient dream
of artificial life.

141
00:18:40,853 --> 00:18:42,878
At least, that’s my hypothesis.

142
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:46,288
Children aren't dolls!

143
00:18:46,358 --> 00:18:51,591
Descartes didn't differentiate man
from machine, animate from inanimate.

144
00:18:51,663 --> 00:18:54,757
He lost his beloved
five-year-old daughter

145
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:57,666
and then named a doll after her,
Francine. He doted on her.

146
00:18:57,736 --> 00:19:00,000
At least that's what they say.

147
00:19:00,072 --> 00:19:01,733
[whirring]

148
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:06,442
Can we get back to reality here?

149
00:19:06,512 --> 00:19:10,812
I'd like your observations
with respect to the Hadaly robot,

150
00:19:10,883 --> 00:19:14,284
model #2052,
manufactured by Locus Solus.

151
00:19:15,754 --> 00:19:16,812
Right.

152
00:19:16,889 --> 00:19:18,982
It's very well designed.

153
00:19:19,057 --> 00:19:23,494
I understand it's a prototype, but
it's intended for particular functions.

154
00:19:23,562 --> 00:19:25,189
[Togusa] Particular functions?

155
00:19:25,264 --> 00:19:28,825
lt's equipped with organs
unnecessary in service robots.

156
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:30,664
[Togusa] Meaning?

157
00:19:30,736 --> 00:19:33,227
[exhales]

158
00:19:33,305 --> 00:19:35,205
[Haraway] It's a sexaroid.

159
00:19:35,274 --> 00:19:39,734
Nothing to brag about to your neighbors,
but hardly illegal.

160
00:19:39,811 --> 00:19:43,941
I get it. Scandal. No wonder
those families settled out of court.

161
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:47,452
When its systems shut down,
the electronic brain reformats.

162
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:52,821
That’s standard protection for
manufacturer's proprietary software.

163
00:19:52,891 --> 00:19:55,416
- But...
- [Togusa] But, what?

164
00:19:55,494 --> 00:19:59,191
We found a file in the audio buffer.
Care to hear it?

165
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,990
[recorded voice] Help me.

166
00:20:03,068 --> 00:20:06,560
[repeating] Help me. Help me.

167
00:20:06,638 --> 00:20:09,072
[recording repeating, beeping]

168
00:20:19,818 --> 00:20:21,581
[recording stops]

169
00:20:24,656 --> 00:20:27,090
[whirring winds down]

170
00:20:30,629 --> 00:20:32,563
[Batou] Thanks for your help.

171
00:20:36,668 --> 00:20:40,695
Uh, one last question.
lt’s none of my business, but...

172
00:20:42,174 --> 00:20:45,575
No, I've never raised a child.

173
00:20:45,644 --> 00:20:49,205
Nothing registered
at the ovum bank.

174
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:51,545
Thank you, Miss...

175
00:20:51,617 --> 00:20:55,314
Haraway.
No need for Miss or Mrs.

176
00:21:02,694 --> 00:21:04,685
[door opens]

177
00:21:07,466 --> 00:21:10,162
[Togusa] She's not really the type
for technical work.

178
00:21:10,235 --> 00:21:14,069
[Batou] Her reports are doubtless full
of unsolicited opinions, just like mine.

179
00:21:14,139 --> 00:21:16,403
[Togusa] Which held you back
from promotion.

180
00:21:16,475 --> 00:21:20,411
[Batou] We secure that gynoid's brain
for the labs at Section 9.

181
00:21:20,479 --> 00:21:22,674
[Togusa] That's the last
we'll see of her.

182
00:21:22,748 --> 00:21:26,184
- [Batou] She your type?
- [Togusa] Actually, I like older women.

183
00:21:26,251 --> 00:21:28,515
- [Togusa] Next?
- [Batou] Follow procedure.

184
00:21:28,587 --> 00:21:31,715
- Investigate the Hadaly inspector?
- [over radio] 09 calling 907.

185
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:34,520
There's been a 602
in the District 201 boathouse.

186
00:21:34,593 --> 00:21:36,424
Victim is inspector for Locus Solus.

187
00:21:36,495 --> 00:21:38,895
Scene secured two minutes
prior to local police.

188
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:42,365
- [Batou] Roger, 907.
- [Togusa] Unbelievable timing.

189
00:21:42,434 --> 00:21:44,095
[Batou] “A fine spring day.

190
00:21:44,169 --> 00:21:47,002
A carriage sprints between
this world and the next."

191
00:21:47,072 --> 00:21:49,734
- [car starts]
- [brakes screeching]

192
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,615
You're all alone here?

193
00:22:03,689 --> 00:22:09,059
Koga got reacquainted with his dinner
and went back with the corpse.

194
00:22:09,127 --> 00:22:11,220
[Batou] What a wimp.

195
00:22:14,366 --> 00:22:17,301
The scene, 22 minutes ago.

196
00:22:25,744 --> 00:22:28,008
You made a rookie
deal with this mess?

197
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:32,642
[lshikawa] Life's a learning curve.
Here's what we've got.

198
00:22:32,718 --> 00:22:35,243
Analysis of victim's brain yields...

199
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:39,620
Jack Volkerson, age 54.
Consignment inspector for Locus Solus.

200
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:43,320
He applied for leave five days ago
and vanished.

201
00:22:44,062 --> 00:22:47,828
Three days ago,
he rented this boathouse.

202
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:51,227
The murder weapon,
kitchen utensils.

203
00:22:51,303 --> 00:22:53,635
Inspection of the area
turned up a vehicle license

204
00:22:53,705 --> 00:22:55,229
linked to organized crime.

205
00:22:56,508 --> 00:22:59,534
We’re checking it out.

206
00:23:02,247 --> 00:23:05,978
Seven credit cards found in jacket,
presumably the victim's.

207
00:23:06,051 --> 00:23:08,281
Investigating transaction history.

208
00:23:28,173 --> 00:23:34,476
38 caliber SW Model 2602.

209
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:37,715
Looks like he ran out of time.

210
00:23:38,216 --> 00:23:41,117
Doubt it would've done him much good.

211
00:23:41,186 --> 00:23:46,055
“An illegally powerful cyborg,"
or maybe a professional faking a psycho.

212
00:23:46,124 --> 00:23:51,061
[over radio] 969 calling 906, 20 seconds
away from the scene, don 't touch.

213
00:23:51,129 --> 00:23:52,994
Not a thing.

214
00:23:54,466 --> 00:23:57,264
[Togusa] Let's leave this to Forensics.

215
00:23:57,335 --> 00:24:01,772
[lshikawa] 907 calling 09.
We're handing the scene over to 969.

216
00:24:03,241 --> 00:24:05,903
- [over radio] 09, Roger.
- [Togusa sighs]

217
00:24:06,511 --> 00:24:08,843
It's my daughter's birthday.

218
00:24:08,914 --> 00:24:11,906
- [lshikawa] Family man, huh?
- I'll drop you off.

219
00:24:11,983 --> 00:24:15,510
- Wrong direction. lshikawa?
- [lshikawa] Not headed his way, either.

220
00:24:15,587 --> 00:24:18,715
Okay.
Daughter's birthday takes priority.

221
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:20,451
You're a cheerful bunch.

222
00:24:20,525 --> 00:24:22,993
The chief showing up at a scene?

223
00:24:23,061 --> 00:24:25,427
The corpse is missing parts, that's why.

224
00:24:25,497 --> 00:24:27,988
The place is all yours.
Take your time.

225
00:24:28,066 --> 00:24:29,966
What’s the big deal
over a local case?

226
00:24:30,035 --> 00:24:33,004
The boss has taken an interest.

227
00:24:33,071 --> 00:24:36,507
[cop] Found it! Divided up in jars
in the refrigerator.

228
00:24:36,575 --> 00:24:40,136
Heart, liver, kidneys,
even the pancreas.

229
00:24:40,212 --> 00:24:42,180
Conscientious bastard.

230
00:24:48,053 --> 00:24:50,886
[footsteps]

231
00:24:57,162 --> 00:25:01,622
Fresh dog food, huh?
Stick to dry food and he'll last longer.

232
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:04,464
I can't feed him that.

233
00:25:10,375 --> 00:25:12,605
You're teamed up with Togusa?

234
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:16,977
Beats being paired off with
a rookie fresh out of training.

235
00:25:17,048 --> 00:25:20,882
For an ex-detective, he's got his uses.
I've got no complaints.

236
00:25:20,952 --> 00:25:26,151
Except that the only one
up to your standards was the Major.

237
00:25:29,794 --> 00:25:33,230
Cut the chatter, lshikawa.

238
00:25:33,298 --> 00:25:38,395
J‘ But everything still holds me

239
00:25:38,470 --> 00:25:41,769
J‘ In my heart

240
